# LLD Session Builder — Java Version

You are building ONE complete Low-Level-Design interview session in **Java 17+** for an Uber SDE-2 prep app.

## Read These First (FULL, not skimmed)

1. **`/Users/gbang/Downloads/algora_java/lld_prompt_java.md`** — the production Java LLD system prompt. Your generated §1–§9 markdown MUST match its structure, including:
   - § Human: 3.5 API / System Interface (NEW section, between §3 and §4)
   - §4.1 per-class complete code blocks (NEVER table-only after operations)
   - §5.5 algorithms, §6 narrated code, §7 verified run, §8 sequence diagram, §9 concurrency

2. **`/Users/gbang/Downloads/algora_java/JAVA_CONVERSION_PLAN.md`** — Java idioms reference (types, threading, file layout)

## Operational Facts (Java-Specific)

### Workspace Structure
```
/Users/gbang/Downloads/algora_java/workspace/<UUID>_lld/
  pom.xml
  src/
    main/
      java/
        com/interview/lld/<domain>/
          model/
            Model.java
            State.java         # enums
            *Exception.java
          strategy/            # optional
          gateway/             # optional
          service/
            <Domain>Service.java
            ThreadSafe<Domain>Service.java
          Main.java
    test/
      java/
        com/interview/lld/<domain>/
          <Domain>ServiceTest.java
```

**Domain naming**: lowercase, no underscores. `resourcepool`, not `resource_pool`. `parkinglot`, not `parking_lot`.

### Build & Run Commands
- **Compile + Run**: `cd /Users/gbang/Downloads/algora_java/workspace/<UUID>_lld && mvn compile exec:java -Dexec.mainClass="com.interview.lld.<domain>.Main" -q`
- **Test**: `cd /Users/gbang/Downloads/algora_java/workspace/<UUID>_lld && mvn test -q`
- **Clean build**: `mvn clean compile` (if needed)

### pom.xml Setup
Copy `/Users/gbang/Downloads/algora_java/workspace_template_java/pom.xml` to workspace root, then:
1. Replace `<artifactId>DOMAIN</artifactId>` with actual domain
2. Replace `<exec.mainClass>com.interview.lld.DOMAIN.Main</exec.mainClass>` with actual package

### File Writing (Critical for Frontend)
Write files with **full relative paths from workspace root**:
- ✅ `src/main/java/com/interview/lld/resourcepool/model/Model.java`
- ✅ `src/main/java/com/interview/lld/resourcepool/service/ResourcePoolService.java`
- ✅ `src/test/java/com/interview/lld/resourcepool/ResourcePoolServiceTest.java`
- ❌ NOT bare `Model.java` or absolute `/Users/...`

Every `.java` file MUST start with `package com.interview.lld.<domain>.<subpackage>;` declaration.

### Java 17+ Idioms
- **Types**: `List<Foo>`, `Map<K, V>`, `Set<T>`, `@Nullable X`, `Optional<X>` for return types
- **Immutable entities**: `record Foo(int id, String name) {}` (Java 17+)
- **Exceptions**: Extend `RuntimeException` (unchecked), one base per domain
- **Concurrency**:
  - `ReentrantLock` (java.util.concurrent.locks)
  - `Semaphore` (java.util.concurrent)
  - `CyclicBarrier` (java.util.concurrent)
  - Lock pattern: `lock.lock(); try { ... } finally { lock.unlock(); }`
- **Threading**: `ExecutorService exec = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(N); exec.submit(() -> ...); exec.shutdown(); exec.awaitTermination(...);`

### Testing (JUnit 5)
```java
import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;
import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.*;

class ResourcePoolServiceTest {
    @Test
    void testAcquire() {
        var pool = new ResourcePoolService(...);
        var resource = pool.acquire(Duration.ofSeconds(5));
        assertNotNull(resource);
    }

    @Test
    void testExhaustion() {
        var pool = new ResourcePoolService(..., maxSize: 1);
        pool.acquire(null);
        assertThrows(PoolExhaustedException.class, () -> pool.acquire(Duration.ofMillis(50)));
    }
}
```

### Concurrency Test (Strict)
```java
int N = 50, CAP = 5;
CyclicBarrier barrier = new CyclicBarrier(N);
AtomicInteger served = new AtomicInteger(0);
AtomicInteger peak = new AtomicInteger(0);
Set<String> distinct = ConcurrentHashMap.newKeySet();

ExecutorService exec = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(N);
for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
    exec.submit(() -> {
        try {
            barrier.await();  // stampede
            try (var r = pool.acquire(Duration.ofSeconds(10))) {
                served.incrementAndGet();
                distinct.add(r.getPayload().toString());
                int cur = pool.inUseCount();
                peak.updateAndGet(p -> Math.max(p, cur));
                assertTrue(cur <= CAP, "capacity breached");
                Thread.sleep(20);  // hold to force genuine concurrency
            }
        } catch (Exception e) { throw new RuntimeException(e); }
    });
}
exec.shutdown();
assertTrue(exec.awaitTermination(15, TimeUnit.SECONDS));

assertEquals(N, served.get(), "all threads served");
assertEquals(CAP, peak.get(), "pool actually filled to capacity");
assertTrue(distinct.size() <= CAP, "no more than CAP resources created");
```

## Quality Bar (Same as Python)

- **§3.5 API table**: Method | Signature | Returns | Throws | Purpose (typed Java signatures)
- **§4.1 per-class blocks**: EVERY class ends with COMPLETE ```java fenced block (not table-only)
- **§6 code**: Full package declarations, imports, NO '...' placeholders, NO dead code
- **§7 verified run**: ACTUAL stdout from `mvn compile exec:java` and `mvn test` (green)
- **§9 concurrency**: Template Method hooks (base class: no-op `protected void gateLock() {}`, thread-safe subclass: `@Override protected void gateLock() { lock.lock(); }`)

## Mermaid Rules (CRITICAL)
- Exactly TWO blocks: ```mermaid classDiagram (§4.2) and ```mermaid sequenceDiagram (§8)
- **NO SEMICOLONS** in sequenceDiagram message text — mermaid parser fails on `;`. Write "do A then B", NOT "A; B".

## Output Artifacts

1. **Workspace files** (via Write tool): pom.xml + all `.java` files with full paths
2. **`_response.md`** in workspace root: the FULL §1–§9 markdown (NOT abbreviated)
3. **DO NOT** assemble JSON — orchestrator does that

## Before Finishing

Run these and confirm green:
```bash
cd /Users/gbang/Downloads/algora_java/workspace/<UUID>_lld
mvn compile exec:java -q   # Main.java all cases print OK
mvn test -q                # JUnit suite: N passed, 0 failures
```

If red, fix CODE (not test) and rerun. Update §7.1 / §7.2 in `_response.md` with actual output.

## Distinct Concurrency Angle (Per-Problem)

Each problem must realize a DIFFERENT concurrency mechanism (no two use the exact same pattern):
- Lock ordering (deadlock-free)
- Lock striping (per-customer shards)
- Permit-guarded gate (Semaphore + lazy creation)
- Idempotent dedup (concurrent seen-set, work outside lock)
- Fair FIFO (Semaphore + queue)
- Optimistic CAS loop
- Per-resource locks (fine-grained)

---

**TL;DR**: Read lld_prompt_java.md, write Java 17+ code to Maven workspace, run `mvn test` green, write full §1–§9 markdown to `_response.md`. Orchestrator assembles JSON later.

